2 types of lists are there in HTML

OL  ==>> ordered list with number
UL ===> Underdered list
    type = "disc"
    type = "square"
    type = "circle"


OL comes with numbers 
    order's number types
    type = capital later: A 
    type = capital later: a 
    type = "1" 
    type="i"  ==> small later in roman number system
    type="I" ==> capital later in roman number system

reversed list can be shown using a attribute: reversed


